Figures To Facts is currently looking for an R Programmer



Figures To Facts is a company specialized in BI dashboard and report
creation on sales and marketing data.

We are a small but fast growing company, working for the largest Fast Moving
Consumer Goods enterprises in the world.


We are currently looking for an R programmer, who will become responsible
for the complete 'data environment' in our company.

Main responsibilities:



-    You will create new functions in R for New Business Development
purposes;
-    You will maintain and create databases in SQL (SQLite, ProgreSQL) based
on multiple data sources;
-   You will structurally perform data quality checks to ensure data
integrity;

-   You will create and maintain web scraping programs;
-   You will update and/or improve existing functions in R;
-   You will optimize and extend a report system created in a Web Based
Environment;

Required:

Programming Skills:

* Thorough knowledge of efficient programming in R;
* Thorough knowledge of handling SQLite, ProgreSQL, Ubuntu and RApache;
* Aptitude in programming and data analysis in order to develop tools for
manipulating, managing and analyzing data;
* Knowledge of Phyton for web scraping purposes;



Very nice to have:
* Knowledge/interest of statistics and econometrics;

* Knowledge/interest in excel programming by VBA;


Personal Skills:

* You are a dynamic team player who works efficiently and in a structured
way;

* You are client focused and you like to communicate with customers;
* You are operational within a short period of time;


Offer:

Competitive reward
Contract type to be discussed
Freelance offers will not be retained

Figures to Facts offices are located in Belgium, Ninove (+/- 25km from
Brussels).





Interested? Don't hesitate to send a statement of interest and CV to
 <mailto:veronique.tack at beeatwork.be> veronique.tack at beeatwork.be.  Mention
FIGURES TO FACTS in the subject.




